**Category:** essay-draft truth statements exposure searle practical-knowledge faith

**Abstract:**
Essay titled "On Truth and Exposure" critiquing the Aristotelian-Thomistic restriction of truth to predicative statements. Argues statements are not pictures but performative speech acts aiming at word-world fit. Uses the example "Es el Señor" to show that knowing God is not having a picture but entering into appropriate relationship. Develops the concept of "adorandus" as gerundive knowledge requiring response.

**AI Recommendation:** Key text on truth and response; develops gerundive/practical knowledge thesis.

